one week after another potential blockbuster, "Ghostbusters II." ; Photo, "The 
Abyss," the year's third underwater thriller, will be opened slowly by a 
cautious Twentieth Century-Fox. ; Photo, "License to Kill," starring Timothy 
Dalton as perennial summer visitor James Bond. ; Photo, "Dead Poet's Society," 
with Robin Williams as an inspirational teacher, will be counterprogrammed 
against "Star Trek V." ; Photo, "Great Balls of Fire," with Dennis Quaid as 
Jerry Lee Lewis, will court music and movie journalists. ; Photo, "Lethal 
Weapon 2," which reunites Mel Gibson and Danny Glover, has garnered "buzz" due 
to research screenings. ; Photo, Moviegoer Jesse Griggs checks out coming 
attractions in the lobby of Mann's Chinese Theatre. JOSE GALVEZ / L.A. Times; 
